Basic Python Example
Here’s a simple Python function:

def greet(name):
    return f"Hello, {name}!"

result = greet("World")
print(result)

Hello, World!

title: My First Blog Post
text:
Working with Data
You can also work with data structures:

numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
squared = [x**2 for x in numbers]
print(f"Original: {numbers}")
print(f"Squared: {squared}")

Original: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
Squared: [1, 4, 9, 16, 25]
